Shader-Based Renewable Energy Farm Visualization
Name: Gunabhiram Aruru
Course: CSCI 4229/5229 Computer Graphics

Current Project Description
---------------------------
This program develops the working prior renewable-energy farm scene into the
final-project codebase. It preserves the handmade textured scene, moving
positional light, animation, navigation, and object inspection while adding
renewable-energy structures and restrained secondary scenery.

The current scene contains:
- three handmade animated wind turbines
- a handmade barn/shed
- a handmade framed greenhouse with separately drawn glazing
- a handmade four-panel solar array with support posts
- four low-poly handmade trees
- a fence and path
- a textured ground plane
- a visible moving positional light

The greenhouse glass is currently an opaque colored placeholder drawn in a
separate function. Real transparency, shaders, wind-flow visualization, and
fog will be implemented in later phases.

Build Instructions
------------------
Run these commands from this directory.

On Linux or macOS:
    make clean
    make

The Makefile compiles with:
    g++ -std=c++11 -Wall -Wextra

Run Instructions
----------------
    ./final

Controls
--------
0                 Inspect the full scene
1                 Inspect turbines only
2                 Inspect barn/farmhouse only
3                 Inspect greenhouse only
4                 Inspect solar-panel array only
5                 Inspect fence and secondary objects
Arrow keys        Rotate overview camera or navigate in first-person mode
PageUp/PageDown   Adjust zoom or field of view
+ or =            Zoom in / decrease field of view
- or _            Zoom out / increase field of view
m                 Cycle orthographic, perspective, and first-person modes
R                 Reset to the default full-scene perspective camera
r                 Pause/resume turbine blade rotation
a                 Toggle axes
l                 Toggle lighting
t                 Toggle textures
Space             Pause/resume automatic light movement
, and .           Move the light angle manually
[ and ]           Lower/raise the light
q or ESC          Exit

Default State
-------------
The program starts in a perspective overview with lighting, textures, depth
testing, moving light, and turbine animation enabled.

Code Reuse and Phase 1 Changes
------------------------------
The handmade turbine, barn, fence, path, ground, BMP loader, lighting,
texture mapping, navigation, and animation are reused from the author's
prior course project.

Phase 1 changes include:
- final-project source, executable, title, and documentation naming
- perspective overview as the initial camera
- object inspection modes 0 through 5
- centered camera presets for each inspection group
- scene drawing refactored into named object-group functions
- updated HUD showing project, camera, inspection, lighting, and texture state

Current object additions include:
- greenhouse frame, roof structure, and separate opaque glass placeholder
- angled photovoltaic panels with handmade supports and specular material
- low-poly trees with handmade trunks and cone canopies

No GLSL shader, GLEW dependency, fog, blending, or real transparency is
included yet.

Textures
--------
Only textures currently used by the program are included:
- textures/grass.bmp
- textures/metal.bmp
- textures/path.bmp
- textures/roof.bmp
- textures/wood.bmp

Known Limitations
-----------------
- Greenhouse glazing is opaque until the later transparency phase.
- Texture and shader-ready asset paths are relative, so run ./final from the
  project directory.
